I developed a Research Assistant using a RAG pipeline, deployed through Streamlit. I used LangChain to integrate multiple knowledge sources, including the Wikipedia API Wrapper, ArXiv API Wrapper, and WebBaseLoader, which allows users to provide a webpage URL and load its content for question answering.
For the RAG flow, the loaded web content is split into chunks, converted into vector embeddings using Ollama Embeddings (open-source), and stored in ChromaDB for semantic retrieval. When a user asks a question, the relevant chunks are retrieved and passed as context to Gemini 2.5 Flash through OpenRouter to generate a context-aware response. The application can also use Wikipedia and ArXiv as tools to retrieve additional research information.
